      <title>Divine Avatar duration now 3 minutes</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=9293#M9293</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Divine Avatar III now has a duration of 3 minutes.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I think it's a nice change; it still doesn't really justify the expense of this AA or give it much added value. However, since it is a longer duration and still carries the heal-over-time component, it does gain some value as a long duration, small value, self-only, manaless heal.&amp;nbsp; Not a big deal, but it could be useful.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I'm interested in seeing the new Depths improvement to Divine Avatar to see if it makes the ability any more potent. Well, I should say, &lt;EM&gt;noticeably&lt;/EM&gt; more potent. I'm not going to get excited if I'm hitting for 50 or 100 more.&amp;nbsp; 500 or 1000 more, is another story, though. I guess we'll wait and see.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Does this change put this into the 'to be bought list' for anyone? I wouldn't imagine so, but I'd like to hear if anyone has new plans on purchasing this AA because of the recent and upcoming change.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
