      <description>Is this better than the old version?  Definitely.  Does it still suck because of the reuse? Also definitely.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It's really too bad that so much time has been wasted on this aa - it's still just a rarely used toy with very little application (honestly, a 3 minute 200 regen/tick aa would have been about the same value) on raids, for xp groups and for soloing.  To make matters worse, there's a Greater Avatar AA in DoN (of all the AA we have, how did turn undead and divine avatar end up getting upgrades?  Does Sony really hate clerics that much?).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Here are 3 different ways I think that avatar could be modified to be useful:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(1)  leave it as is, 15 minute reuse.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(2)  instead of a melee only buff, make it also affect nukes and heals (25% improvement at level 1, scaled to 150% at level 6) - 30 minute reuse.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(3)  leave it as is for effect, but make it a self-group buff, 30 sec duration, 30 minute reuse.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Any of those options would at least make it a viable raid/group tool.</description>
